'''Katayama Hachiman Shrine''' (片山八幡社) is a {{ill|Hachiman shrine|ja|八幡神社|12=draft|12=draft}} ({{ill|Shinto shrine|ja|神社|12=draft|12=draft}}) located in {{ill|Komaki, Aichi|ja|小牧市|12=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|Aichi Prefecture|ja|愛知県|12=draft|12=draft}}. It is a {{ill|ronsha|ja|論社|12=draft|12=draft}} (theory-associated shrine) listed as "Katayama Shrine" in the {{ill|Engishiki Jinmyōchō|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|2=ja|3=延喜式神名帳|4=zh|5=延喜式神名帳|6=simple|7=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|2=ja|3=延喜式神名帳|4=zh|5=延喜式神名帳|6=simple|7=Engishiki Jinmyocho|ja|延喜式神名帳|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|2=ja|3=延喜式神名帳|4=zh|5=延喜式神名帳|6=simple|7=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|2=ja|3=延喜式神名帳|4=zh|5=延喜式神名帳|6=simple|7=Engishiki Jinmyocho|12=draft|12=draft}} under {{ill|Owari Province|ja|尾張国|12=draft|12=draft}} and is a former {{ill|Gōsha|ja|郷社|12=draft|12=draft}}.

== Deities ==
* [[Emperor Ōjin]]
* [[Sukunabikona-no-Mikoto]]

== History ==
According to the shrine's history, its foundation dates back to {{ill|Jōgan|ja|貞観|12=draft|12=draft}} 13 (871), on May 15. It is said to have been established by enshrining the deities of {{ill|Iwashimizu Hachiman Shrine|ja|石清水八幡宮|12=draft|12=draft}} in present-day {{ill|Yawata, Kyoto|ja|八幡市|12=draft|12=draft}}, through a {{ill|bunrei|ja|分霊|12=draft|12=draft}} (division of spirit).

== External Links ==
* [http://www.kskn.co.jp/komakiview4.html Katayama Hachiman Shrine (Komaki Service)]

