'''Katayama Hachiman Shrine''' (片山八幡社) is a {{ill|Hachiman shrine|lt=Hachiman shrine|lt=Hachiman Shrine|ja|八幡神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hachiman shrine|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 八幡宮}} ([[:en:Shinto shrine|Shinto shrine]]) located in [[:en:Komaki|Komaki, Aichi]], [[:en:Aichi Prefecture|Aichi Prefecture]]. It is a {{ill|ronsha|ja|論社|1=candidate shrines|2=ja|3=論社|lt=candidate|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/ronsha|13=User:Immanuelle/candidate shrines|1=Engishiki_Jinmyōchō#Ronsha|2=ja|3=延喜式神名帳|4=zh|5=延喜式神名帳|6=simple|7=Engishiki_Jinmyocho|lt=Ronsha}}}} (theory-associated shrine) listed as "Katayama Shrine" in the {{ill|Engishiki Jinmyōchō|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|2=ja|3=延喜式神名帳|4=zh|5=延喜式神名帳|6=simple|7=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|2=ja|3=延喜式神名帳|4=zh|5=延喜式神名帳|6=simple|7=Engishiki|ja|延喜式神名帳|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|2=ja|3=延喜式神名帳|4=zh|5=延喜式神名帳|6=simple|7=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|2=ja|3=延喜式神名帳|4=zh|5=延喜式神名帳|6=simple|7=Engishiki|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Engishiki Jinmyōchō|13=User:Immanuelle/Engishiki Jinmyōchō|qq=}} under [[:en:Owari Province|Owari Province]] and is a former {{ill|Gōsha|ja|郷社|1=Gō-sha|qid=Q134917316}}{{efn|District Shrines|lt=Ken-sha|1=modern system of ranked Shinto shrines|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Gōsha|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 近代社格制度|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q712534}}.
== Deities == * [[:en:Emperor Ōjin|Emperor Ōjin]] * [[Sukunabikona-no-Mikoto]]
== History == According to the shrine's history, its foundation dates back to [[:en:Zhenguan|Jōgan]] 13 (871), on May 15. It is said to have been established by enshrining the deities of [[:en:Iwashimizu Hachimangū|Iwashimizu Hachiman Shrine]] in present-day [[:en:Yawata|Yawata, Kyoto]], through a [[:en:Bunrei|bunrei]] (division of spirit).
